04793nam a22007095i 9781478012009DE-B159720210526051534.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210526t20202020ncu    fo  d z      eng d  a2019041096  a97814780120097 a10.1515/97814780120092doi  a(DE-B1597)552061  a(OCoLC)1135939158  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  ancucUS-NC00aML3477.8.L67bH46 2020 7aMUS0150002bisacsh04a781.63089/9155079492231 aHemmasi, Farzaneh, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aTehrangeles Dreaming :bIntimacy and Imagination in Southern California's Iranian Pop Music /cFarzaneh Hemmasi. 1aDurham : bDuke University Press, c[2020] 4cÂ©2020  a1 online resource (264 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction -- t1. The Capital of 6/8 -- t2. Iranian Popular Music and History: Views from Tehrangeles -- t3. Expatriate Erotics, Homeland Moralities -- t4. Iran as a Singing Woman -- t5. A Nation in Recovery -- tConclusion: Forty Years -- tNotes -- tReferences -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aLos Angeles, called Tehrangeles because it is home to the largest concentration of Iranians outside of Iran, is the birthplace of a distinctive form of postrevolutionary pop music. Created by professional musicians and media producers fleeing Iran's revolutionary-era ban on "immoral" popular music, Tehrangeles pop has been a part of daily life for Iranians at home and abroad for decades. In Tehrangeles Dreaming Farzaneh Hemmasi draws on ethnographic fieldwork in Los Angeles and musical and textual analysis to examine how the songs, music videos, and television made in Tehrangeles express modes of Iranianness not possible in Iran. Exploring Tehrangeles pop producers' complex commercial and political positioning and the histories, sensations, and fantasies their music makes available to global Iranian audiences, Hemmasi shows how unquestionably Iranian forms of Tehrangeles popular culture exemplify the manner in which culture, media, and diaspora combine to respond to the Iranian state and its political transformations. The transnational circulation of Tehrangeles culture, she contends, transgresses Iran's geographical, legal, and moral boundaries while allowing all Iranians the ability to imagine new forms of identity and belonging.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aIranian diaspora. 0aIranianszCaliforniazLos AngelesxEthnic identity. 0aIranianszCaliforniazLos AngelesxMusic. 0aMusicxPolitical aspectszIranxHistoryy20th century. 0aPopular musiczCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistory and criticism. 0aPopular musiczIranxHistory and criticism. 7aMUSIC / Ethnomusicology.2bisacsh  aglobal Iranian diaspora.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069631808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478012009zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478012009423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478012009.jpg  a978-3-11-069631-8  DUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070474-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_DUK_AL